HEADWORD: Dasewe
<hw>Dase"we</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>dasewen</ets>, <ets>daswen</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>dysegian</ets> to be
foolish.]</ety> <def>To become dim-sighted; to become dazed or
dazzled.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chauscer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

